Migration Plan
1. Project Setup
 Update Dependencies
Ensure all Radix UI components are up to date
Update React and related dependencies
Verify compatibility with Astro
2. Directory Structure
 Create Missing Directories
src/components/ui (for shadcn/ui components)
src/lib (for utilities and shared code)
src/hooks (for custom React hooks)
3. Component Migration
 Migrate UI Components
Convert components to use shadcn/ui patterns
Update any Radix UI components to their shadcn/ui equivalents
Ensure all components use Tailwind CSS for styling
4. Styling
 Update Styling
Review and update color theming
Convert any CSS-in-JS to Tailwind classes
Ensure responsive design works as expected
5. State Management
 Review State Management
Check for any state management libraries (e.g., Zustand, Jotai)
Update or replace as needed
6. Testing
 Set Up Testing
Configure Vitest for unit testing
Add tests for components and utilities
7. Build & Deployment
 Update Build Configuration
Configure Astro build settings
Update Vercel deployment settings
8. Documentation
 Update Documentation
Document the migration process
Update README with new setup instructions
9. Testing & Validation
 Test the Application
Test all components and features
Verify performance and accessibility
10. Deployment
 Deploy the Application
Deploy to Vercel
Monitor for any issues
Next Steps
Start with the project setup and dependency updates
Migrate components one by one, testing as you go
Update styling and state management as needed
Test thoroughly before deployment
